{{More citations needed|date=October 2010}}

The '''Lambda 10 Project''' is a national [[wikt:clearing house|clearinghouse]] of information pertaining to [[LGBT]] issues in [[United States|American]] [[fraternities and sororities]]. The [[organization]] works to heighten the visibility of [[Coming out|out]] members (chiefly [[university]] [[student]]s), and offers educational resources related to [[sexual orientation]] and the fraternity/sorority experience.<ref name="glbtq">{{Cite web | last =Kaczorowski | first =Craig | title =Fraternities and Sororities | work =glbtq: An Encyclopedia of Gay, Lesbian, Bisexual, Transgender, and Queer Culture | publisher =glbtq, Inc. | date =2004-02-12| url =http://www.glbtq.com/social-sciences/fraternities,2.html}}</ref>

The Lambda 10 Project was founded in the autumn of 1995 at [[Indiana University Bloomington|Indiana University]] in [[Bloomington, Indiana]]; it is currently [[Headquarters|headquartered]] in the University's Office of Student Ethics and Anti-harassment Programs.

Among the organization's offerings are an index of [[lecture]]rs available for events; lists of [[Internet forum|forum]]s concerning LGBT "[[Fraternities and sororities|Greek life]]"; and a repository of [[magazine]] articles, [[website]]s, and pertinent [[news]] stories. Working with the renowned LGBT [[publisher]] [[Alyson Publications]], '''Lambda 10''' also compiled and released three [[Anthology|anthologies]] of [[Homosexuality|homosexual]] and [[Bisexuality|bisexual]] students' Greek experiences: ''Out on Fraternity Row: Personal Accounts of Being Gay in a College Fraternity'' (1998), ''Secret Sisters: Stories of Being Lesbian and Bisexual in a College Sorority'' (2001) and ''Brotherhood: Gay Life in College Fraternities'' (2005).<ref name="Lambda 10">{{cite web |url=http://www.lambda10.org|work=Lambda 10 Project |publisher=Campus Pride, Inc.|accessdate=2009-12-03 |title=National Clearinghouse for Gay, Lesbian, Bisexual, Transgender Fraternity & Sorority Issues}}</ref>

Lambda 10 Project is an educational initiative of [[Campus Pride]], an [[United States|American]] national [[nonprofit]] [[501(c)(3)#501.28c.29.283.29|501(c)(3)]] organization which serves [[lesbian]], [[gay]], [[bisexuality|bisexual]] and [[transgender]] ([[LGBT]]) and [[straight ally|ally]] [[student]] leaders and/or [[student society|campus organization]].  It is an associate member of the [[Association of Fraternity Advisors]] and serves as a resource for the leaders of numerous national and international fraternities and sororities.

The Project created an educational resource titled Out on Fraternity Row: Personal Accounts of Being Gay in a College Fraternity released by Alyson Publications, Inc in 1998, Secret Sisters: Stories of Being Lesbian & Bisexual in a College Sorority released by Alyson Publications, Inc. in 2001 and recently Brotherhood: Gay Life in College Fraternities released by Alyson Publications, Inc. in October 2005.

